
                                RANDWEL
                     Select random welcome screens
                for PCBoard and most other BBS programs.

                     Copyright 1992 Samuel H. Smith

                 Another quick-n-dirty freebie utility
                       courtesy of The Tool Shop
                       (818) 891-6780 (free line)


                                 Usage
                                 -----

                          randwel CONFIG_FILE

                                Example
                                -------

                          randwel randwel.cfg

 Insert in your BOARD.BAT file just prior to loading the BBS software.


                           Config file format
                           ------------------

Line 1 contains the DESTINATION of a DOS COPY command for your active
welcome screen.

The remaining lines each specify a possible alternate welcome file.


                        Sample RANDWEL.CFG file
                        -----------------------

c:\pcb\gen\welcome?.
c:\pcb\gen\welcome?.001
c:\pcb\gen\welcome?.002
c:\pcb\gen\welcome?.003
c:\pcb\gen\welcome?.004
c:\pcb\gen\welcome?.005
c:\pcb\gen\welcome?.006
c:\pcb\gen\welcome?.007
c:\pcb\gen\welcome?.008
c:\pcb\gen\welcome?.009
c:\pcb\gen\welcome?.010


This config file will randomly select c:\pcb\gen\welcome.001 through
c:\pcb\gen\welcome.010 and copy it to c:\pcb\gen\welcome.  The ?
prior to the . causes a welcomeg (graphics version of welcome) to also
be copied.  If you are not running pcboard or you prefer not to copy
both graphic and non-graphic welcome files, please remove the ? from
each line of the config file.

